		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Harshness aside, this sub-forum is for discussion of NES emulator <em>development</em>, not consumption. There are probably hundreds of sites which keep up with the latest emulator releases and "scene" happenings. On-topic postings here are questions about emulation and ideas/source code for use in emulators.
<br />
<br />The point of limiting discussion to specific topics in each sub-forum is that it allows people with limited time to quickly filter out content they're not interested in. There are plenty of people interested in discussion of emulator development and implementation, but not in the latest release of emulator X, so this limitation is practical.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
